com.kandbnutrition.animation

Class DoubleTransition

  • java.lang.Object
    • javafx.animation.Animation
      • javafx.animation.Transition
        • com.kandbnutrition.animation.DoubleTransition

  • public class DoubleTransition
extends javafx.animation.Transition
    This Transition animates/changes any DoubleProperty over a duration. This is done by updating the the property at a regular interval.

    It starts from the fromValue if provided else uses the properties's original value.

    It stops at the toValue value if provided else it will use start value plus byValue.

    The toValue takes precedence if both toValue and byValue are specified.

    Code Segment Example: 

     
 import snap.javafx.*;
 
 ...
 
     DoubleProperty positionProp = aSplitPane.getDividers().get(0).positionProperty();
     
     DoubleTransition dt = new DoubleTransition(Duration.millis(500), positionProp);
     dt.setFromValue(1);
     dt.setToValue(0.5);
     dt.play();
 
 ...
    See Also:
    Transition, Animation

    • Property Detail

      • duration

        public final javafx.beans.property.ObjectProperty<javafx.util.Duration> durationProperty
        The duration of this FadeTransition.

        It is not possible to change the duration of a running FadeTransition. If the value of duration is changed for a running FadeTransition, the animation has to be stopped and started again to pick up the new value.

        Note: While the unit of duration is a millisecond, the granularity depends on the underlying operating system and will in general be larger. For example animations on desktop systems usually run with a maximum of 60fps which gives a granularity of ~17 ms.

        See Also:
        getDuration(), setDuration(Duration)
